#compdef testground
# =============================================================================
# testground — Protocol Labs / IPFS Foundation's "platform for
#                testing, benchmarking, and simulating distributed
#                and p2p systems at scale" — a Go CLI + daemon
#                that orchestrates large-scale distributed-system
#                test runs across local Docker, local processes,
#                or Kubernetes clusters.  Originally built by
#                Protocol Labs as the test harness for libp2p
#                (the IPFS networking stack), now used for
#                distributed-system testing across multiple
#                blockchain projects, p2p protocols, and HPC
#                workloads.  Architecture:
#                  - TEST PLANS: Go modules implementing a
#                    standardized test interface
#                  - COMPOSITIONS: TOML manifest specifying
#                    instance count + test parameters + runner
#                    + builder for a test run
#                  - BUILDERS: convert test plan source to
#                    deployable artifact ('docker:go', 'exec:go')
#                  - RUNNERS: deploy artifacts and orchestrate
#                    the test run ('local:exec', 'local:docker',
#                    'cluster:k8s')
#                  - SIDECAR: per-instance traffic shaping,
#                    network partitioning, latency injection
#                    via Linux netem
#                  - SYNC SERVICE: pubsub-style barrier
#                    coordination between test instances
#                  - METRICS / ASSETS COLLECTION: gather logs,
#                    InfluxDB metrics, profile dumps after run
#                Used to validate libp2p's gossipsub at 10,000+
#                node scale, BitTorrent DHT correctness, IPFS
#                bitswap, Filecoin storage proofs, and many
#                other p2p/distributed-system invariants.
#
# Author:  Protocol Labs / IPFS Foundation team — Adin Schmahmann
#          + Anton Evangelatov + Raúl Kripalani + 50+ contributors
#          (testground originated at Protocol Labs in 2019 as a
#          libp2p testing tool; now maintained by the broader IPFS
#          + Filecoin + libp2p community).
# Source:  https://github.com/testground/testground
#          https://github.com/testground/testground/blob/master/main.go
# CLI:     main.go + pkg/cmd/*.go — uses `urfave/cli/v2`
#          (already documented in taxonomy) for subcommand
#          routing.  Headline observability library: `go.uber.org/
#          zap` for high-performance structured logging
#          throughout the testground daemon, test plan
#          orchestration, and result collection.
# Library: go.uber.org/zap
#          ("Blazing fast, structured, leveled logging in Go" —
#           Uber Engineering — released 2017 as Uber's response
#           to the performance overhead of logrus + glog in
#           high-throughput Go services.  zap achieves 4-10x
#           faster logging than logrus by avoiding reflection,
#           using a typed-field API, and minimizing allocations.
#           Industry-standard logger for Kubernetes ecosystem
#           tools, distributed-systems infrastructure, and any
#           Go service where logging hot-paths matter.  Two API
#           styles: `zap.Logger` (typed fields, fastest) and
#           `zap.SugaredLogger` (printf-style ergonomics, ~2x
#           slower but still faster than logrus).)
# License: Apache-2.0 (testground); MIT (zap)
# Status:  testground — 434+ stars on testground/testground;
#          actively used in IPFS/libp2p/Filecoin testing
#          pipelines; zap — 24500+ stars on uber-go/zap, top-30
#          Go GitHub project by stars, foundational logger
#          dependency of Kubernetes ecosystem (kubebuilder /
#          operator-sdk / many controllers), CockroachDB,
#          TiKV-go-client, vmware-tanzu projects, and thousands
#          of Go services across cloud infrastructure.
#
